table_description: AWS VPC Network Address Translation Gateway

columns.name: nat_gateway_id
columns.description: The ID of the NAT gateway.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) specifying the NAT gateway.

columns.name: nat_gateway_addresses
columns.description: Information about the IP addresses and network interface associated with the NAT gateway.

columns.name: state
columns.description: The current state of the NAT gateway (pending | failed | available | deleting | deleted).

columns.name: create_time
columns.description: The date and time the NAT gateway was created.

columns.name: vpc_id
columns.description: The ID of the VPC in which the NAT gateway is located.

columns.name: subnet_id
columns.description: The ID of the subnet in which the NAT gateway is located.

columns.name: delete_time
columns.description: The date and time the NAT gateway was deleted, if applicable.

columns.name: failure_code
columns.description: If the NAT gateway could not be created, specifies the error code for the failure. (InsufficientFreeAddressesInSubnet | Gateway.NotAttached | InvalidAllocationID.NotFound | Resource.AlreadyAssociated | InternalError | InvalidSubnetID.NotFound).

columns.name: failure_message
columns.description: If the NAT gateway could not be created, specifies the error message for the failure.

columns.name: provisioned_bandwidth
columns.description: Reserved. If you need to sustain traffic greater than the documented limits (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-nat-gateway.html).

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags that are attached to NAT gateway.
